<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="sat-layout">
    <div class="passage-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Passage</div>
      <div class="passage-source">SAT-style practice passage</div>
      <div class="passage-text">Practice passage for Logical Transitions. The full lesson content for this question focuses on applying the core skill: <strong>logical transitions</strong>.<br><br>Read this passage carefully and answer the question on the right based solely on what is stated or implied here.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Logical Transitions</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which choice best demonstrates the key skill taught in this lesson?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>Answer option A — tests core concept application</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>Answer option B — correct answer for this question</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>Answer option C — common misconception trap</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>Answer option D — too broad or off-topic</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> Option B correctly applies the skill of logical transitions. It directly addresses the passage's evidence without overstating or understating the author's point.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Review the passage carefully. Look for the option that most directly addresses what the question asks — without going beyond what the passage actually states.</div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="sat-layout">
    <div class="passage-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Passage</div>
      <div class="passage-source">SAT-style practice passage</div>
      <div class="passage-text">Second practice passage for Logical Transitions. This question tests a slightly different application of the same core skill.<br><br>Pay attention to the specific wording of both the passage and the question stem before selecting your answer.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Logical Transitions</div>
      <div class="q-text">Based on the passage, which choice most accurately reflects the author's point?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>A partially correct answer that misses a key qualifier</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>An answer that contradicts the passage's main claim</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>The correct answer that precisely matches the passage</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>An answer that introduces information not in the passage</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> Option C precisely captures the author's meaning. It neither overstates nor understates what the passage actually says.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Compare each option carefully against the passage. The correct answer will be directly supported — nothing more, nothing less.</div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'C')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="sat-layout">
    <div class="passage-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Passage</div>
      <div class="passage-source">SAT-style practice passage</div>
      <div class="passage-text">Third practice passage for Logical Transitions. This is the most challenging question in this lesson — it tests the nuanced application of the skill in a complex passage context.<br><br>Take your time and apply the full strategy before selecting your answer.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Logical Transitions</div>
